OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F306A1748573300
OL,3,C'Young people and black workers at
OL,4,Chighest risk of workplace surveillance'
OL,6,FIts research suggested those in low-
OL,7,Fskilled roles ` where worker retention
OL,8,Fmay be seen as less critical ` and low-
OL,9,Fautonomy jobs ` where there might be
OL,10,Flower levels of employee trust ` as
OL,11,Fwell as those not in a union are most
OL,12,Flikely to be subject to monitoring at
OL,13,Fwork.
OL,15,FYoung workers aged 16 to 29 came out
OL,16,Fas being at high risk.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
