OL,3,C'Young people and black workers at
OL,4,Chighest risk of workplace surveillance'
OL,6,FBlack employees were also seen as
OL,7,Flikely to face surveillance, with high
OL,8,Frates of low autonomy and lower-
OL,9,Fskilled work, although greater levels
OL,10,Fof union representation.
OL,12,FAmong workers in the private sector,
OL,13,Fmen were found to be at higher risk of
OL,14,Fsurveillance across all three risk
OL,15,Ffactor measures.
