OL,3,C'Young people and black workers at
OL,4,Chighest risk of workplace surveillance'
OL,6,FThe IPPR is calling on the Government
OL,7,Fto introduce new legislation that
OL,8,Fgives people "a genuine voice over how
OL,9,Fthey are monitored at work" through
OL,10,Fnew legal rights to consultation `
OL,11,Fsimilar to those with redundancy law `
OL,12,Fand more transparency requirements,
OL,13,Fcompelling employers to disclose what
OL,14,Fdata is collected, why, and how it
OL,15,Fwill be used.
