OL,3,C'Young people and black workers at
OL,4,Chighest risk of workplace surveillance'
OL,6,FJoseph Evans, IPPR researcher and co-
OL,7,Fauthor of the report, said while
OL,8,Ftechnology has "evolved really
OL,9,Frapidly", legislation has not kept up
OL,10,Fwith the pace of change "so at the
OL,11,Fmoment many of these practices are not
OL,12,Fillegal but what we don't have is a
OL,13,Fmechanism to control them where
OL,14,Fsurveillance does tip over into
OL,15,Fpotential breaches of privacy or
OL,16,Ffreedom of expression and association
OL,17,Fin the workplace".
OL,19,FHe said surveillance can have "quite
OL,20,Fnegative impacts on people in terms of
OL,21,Ftheir health and stress and anxiety".
