OL,3,C'Young people and black workers at
OL,4,Chighest risk of workplace surveillance'
OL,6,F"As part of their wider changes to
OL,7,Femployment rights, through the
OL,8,FEmployment Rights Bill, there should
OL,9,Fbe substantive new rights to negotiate
OL,10,Fand consult over surveillance. And
OL,11,Fspecifically adapting pieces of
OL,12,Flegislation like the Trade Union and
OL,13,FLabour Relations Act to provide the
OL,14,Fnew mechanism for workers to be able
OL,15,Fto negotiate over surveillance.
OL,17,F"Implicit in the right to negotiate is
OL,18,Fthat it would give workers the right
OL,19,Fto challenge if they felt it
OL,20,F(surveillance) was excessive or
OL,21,Funfair."
